est Africa]], postponed to 9\u201315 September <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scifest.org.za/4177-2/|title=Scifest Africa 2020 Postponed|date=2020-03-17|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n*[[WWE Live]] South Africa, postponed until September 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prowrestling.com/wwe-reschedules-upcoming-south-africa-tour-due-to-coronavirus/|title=WWE Reschedules Upcoming South Africa Tour Due To Coronavirus|date=2020-03-20|website=ProWrestling.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n'''Religious & Spiritual'''\n*[[Sadhguru]] visit to Isha, South Africa 2\u20135 April cancelled.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kaggere |first1=Niranjan |title=Coronavirus: Sadhguru Jaggi Vasudev suspends all Isha Yoga Centre programmes |url=https://www.deccanherald.com/city/coronavirus-sadhguru-jaggi-vasudev-suspends-all-isha-yoga-centre-programmes-814464.html |work=Deccan Herald |accessdate=23 March 2020 }}</ref>\n*Church activities of the [[Dutch Reformed Church]], suspended and moved to WhatsApp groups.{{Citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n*[[Zion Christian Church]] (ZCC) Easter pilgrimage, cancelled until further notice.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/trips-to-moria-on-hold-until-further-notice-over-coronavirus-pandemic-zcc-tells-congregants-20200317|title=Trips to Moria on hold until further notice over coronavirus pandemic, ZCC tells congregants|website=news24.com|date=17 March 2020|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n*[[Muslim Judicial Council]] (MJC) suspends [[Friday prayer]]<nowiki/>s but keeps mosques open. As of Sunday, 22 March, mosques have closed but the call to prayer will still be given.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/coronavirus-mjc-suspends-jumuah-prayers-but-no-call-to-close-mosques-20200318|title=Coronavirus: MJC suspends Jumuah prayers, but no call to close mosques|date=2020-03-18|website=News24|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n* Chief Rabbi [[Warren Goldstein]] suspends Synagogues.<ref>{{cite news |title=South Africa's shuls close to stop spread of coronavirus |url=https://www.sajr.co.za/news-and-articles/2020/03/19/south-africa-s-shuls-close-to-stop-spread-of-coronavirus |work=South Africa Jewish Report |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Traditional circumcision schools in Eastern Cape suspended.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sizani |first1=Mkhuseli |title=Coronavirus: Traditional circumcision schools in Eastern Cape suspended |url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/coronavirus-traditional-circumcision-schools-in-eastern-cape-suspended-20200323 |accessdate=|website=News24}}</ref>\n\n'''Expo & Trade shows'''\n\n* HuntEx, postponed until unknown future date<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huntex.net/|title=HuntEx2020 {{!}} Ten Years Inspiring Adventure|website=www.huntex.net|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* DecorEx Cape Town & Durban, postponed until 2021<ref>{{cite web|url=https://decorex.co.za/|title=HOME|website=Decorex Africa|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* Tyrexpo, postponed to '''4 -6 August 2020''' <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tyrexpoafrica.com/attention.php|title=Tyrexpo Africa 2020|website=www.tyrexpoafrica.com|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n* Power & Electricity World expo, postponed until '''20-21 August 2020'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.terrapinn.com/exhibition/power-electricity-world-africa/Event-Postponement.stm|title=Event Postponement {{!}} Power & Electricity|date=2020-03-23|website=Power & Electricity World Africa 2020|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n\n'''Other'''\n*[[University of Pretoria]], [[University of Cape Town]], [[Stellenbosch University]], [[Rhodes University]], [[University of KwaZulu Natal]] and [[Durban University of Technology]] graduation ceremonies cancelled or postponed until further notice.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ewn.co.za/2020/03/13/stellenbosch-uct-cancel-upcoming-graduations-due-to-coronavirus|title=STELLENBOSCH, UCT CANCEL UPCOMING GRADUATIONS DUE TO CORONAVIRUS|last1=Kassen|first1=Jarita|website=EWN|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/coronavirus-in-sa-uct-graduations-suspended-amid-covid-19-concerns-20200314|title=Coronavirus in SA: UCT graduations suspended amid Covid-19 concerns|last1=McCain|first1=Nicole|website=News24|date=14 March 2020|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sowetanlive.co.za/news/south-africa/2020-03-16-universities-cancelling-in-person-classes-due-to-coronavirus/|title=Universities cancelling in-person classes due to coronavirus|website=SowetanLIVE|language=en-ZA|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.up.ac.za/news/post_2881150-update-postponement-of-contact-classes-and-rescheduling-of-academic-calendar- |title = UPDATE: Postponement of contact classes and rescheduling of academic calendar}}</ref>\n*[[List of comic book conventions|Comic Con]] Cape Town, postponed to 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iol.co.za/entertainment/whats-on/cape-town/comic-con-cape-town-postponed-to-2021-45138721|title=Comic Con Cape Town postponed to 2021|website=www.iol.co.za|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*Agricultural events such as the [[Pietermaritzburg]] Royal Show, SA Cheese Festival, Qualit\u00e9 Awards Dinner, and Agri-Expo Western Cape Youth Show, cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foodformzansi.co.za/covid-19-farmers-urged-to-protect-themselves-workers/|title=COVID-19: Farmers urged to protect themselves, workers|last=Ngcakani|first=Noluthando|date=2020-03-16|website=Food For Mzansi|language=en-ZA|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*[[Wimpy (restaurant)|Wimpy]] [[Lifesaving South Africa]], national championships cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iol.co.za/sport/wimpy-lifesaving-south-africa-national-championships-cancelled-44956403|title=Wimpy Lifesaving South Africa National Championships cancelled|website=www.iol.co.za|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*[[Scouts South Africa]], all Scouting activity suspended until schools reopen.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scouts.org.za/2020/03/16/scouting-suspended-in-response-to-covid-19/|title=Scouting suspended in response to COVID-19|website=www.scouts.org.za|date=16 March 2020|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*The [[Johannesburg|City of Johannesburg]], all public facilities closed indefinitely including public swimming pools, recreational and civic centres, stadiums, libraries, sporting facilities, and the [[Johannesburg Zoo]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://citizen.co.za/news/south-africa/government/2257497/city-of-joburg-closes-all-public-facilities-including-pools-theatres-and-the-zoo/|title=City of Joburg closes all public facilities, including pools, theatres and the zoo |agency=News24 Wire |website=The Citizen|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*The [[EThekwini Metropolitan Municipality|Ethekhwini Metropolitan Municipality]] closed all of [[Durban]]'s public facilities including swimming pools, beaches, libraries, community halls, and museums while restrictions have been put in place for the [[Durban Art Gallery]] and cemeteries to only allow 50 people at a time.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://businesstech.co.za/news/lifestyle/383319/durban-bans-swimming-at-the-beach/|title=Durban bans swimming at the beach|last=Writer|first=Staff|website=businesstech.co.za|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*[[Fake news]] spread to the effect that [[5G|5G cellular]] technology was the true cause of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] symptoms.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://citizen.co.za/lifestyle/technology/2263396/zweli-mkhize-says-5g-causing-covid-19-deaths-is-just-fake-news/|title=Zweli Mkhize says \u20185G causing Covid-19 deaths\u2019 is just fake news|last=Cilliers|first=Charles|website=The Citizen|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> \n\n===Travel===\nPresident [[Cyril Ramaphosa]] announced that from 18 March 2020, a travel ban will be imposed on foreign nationals travelling from high-risk countries and that visas for travellers from those countries have been cancelled.<ref name=\"presidency61\"/>\n\n====Bans====\n[[File:CoVid-19 South African travel bans.svg|thumb|right|Travel bans {{As of|alt=as of 2020-03-19.|2020|03|19}}]]\n*{{flagdeco|China}} [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in mainland China|China]]\n*{{flagdeco|France}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]]<ref>{{Cite news\n|url=https://www.businessinsider.co.za/the-list-of-countries-with-travel-banned-to-south-africa-2020-3\n|title=France is now also on South Africa's Covid-19 travel ban list.\n|date=2020-03-19\n|publisher=Business Insider SA\n|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n*{{flagdeco|Germany}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany|Germany]]\n*{{flagdeco|Iran}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran|Iran]]\n*{{flagdeco|Italy}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|Italy]]\n*{{flagdeco|South Korea}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Korea|South Korea]]\n*{{flagdeco|Spain}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain|Spain]]\n*{{flagdeco|UK}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|UK]]\n*{{flagdeco|USA}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|USA]]\n\n====Border post closures====\nFrom 16 March, 35 of 53 [[List of ports of entry in South Africa|land ports]] were shut down and 2 of the 8 sea ports were closed<ref name=\"presidency61\"/> for passengers and crew changes: [[Mossel Bay#Harbour|Mossel Bay]] and [[Saldanha, Western Cape#Port|Saldanha]].<ref name=\"bisa-ports\">{{cite news\n|title=Here are all the border posts South Africa is closing to combat Covid-19\n|url=https://www.businessinsider.co.za/these-are-the-border-posts-south-africa-is-closing-against-the-coronavirus-2020-3\n|accessdate=2020-03-16 |work=Business Insider South Africa}}</ref> On 19 March, it was announced by [[Minister of Public Works and Infrastructure (South Africa)|Minister of Public Works and Infrastructure]] [[Patricia de Lille]] that the government would erect and repair 40&nbsp;km of fencing to the east and west of the Beitbridge border post between South Africa and [[Zimbabwe]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://businesstech.co.za/news/government/383143/massive-border-fence-between-south-africa-and-zimbabwe-to-combat-coronavirus-spread/|title=Massive border fence between South Africa and Zimbabwe to combat coronavirus spread|last=News|first=S. A.|website=businesstech.co.za|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n====Advisories====\n[[File:CoVid-19 South African travel advisories.svg|thumb|right|Travel advisories {{as of|alt=as of 2020-03-15|2020|03|15}}]][[file:COVID-19 Outbreak World Map-Deaths.svg|thumb|right|Countries with confirmed cases (red) and deaths (black)]]Effective as of 15 March 2020, the government advised against all travel to China, the EU, Iran, South Korea, UK, and the USA; and discouraged all non-essential domestic travel, particularly by air, rail, taxi, and bus.<ref name=\"presidency61\"/>\n\n*{{flagdeco|China}} China\n*{{flagdeco|EU}} [[European Union]]\n**{{flagdeco|Austria}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Austria|Austria]]\n**{{flagdeco|Belgium}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belgium|Belgium]]\n**{{flagdeco|Bulgaria}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bulgaria|Bulgaria]]\n**{{flagdeco|Croatia}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Croatia|Croatia]]\n**{{flagdeco|Cyprus}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Cyprus|Cyprus]]\n**{{flagdeco|Czechia}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic|Czechia]]\n**{{flagdeco|Denmark}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Denmark|Denmark]]\n**{{flagdeco|Estonia}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Estonia|Estonia]]\n**{{flagdeco|Finland}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Finland|Finland]]\n**{{flagdeco|France}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]]\n**{{flagdeco|Germany}} Germany\n**{{flagdeco|Greece}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Greece|Greece]]\n**{{flagdeco|Hungary}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Hungary|Hungary]]\n**{{flagdeco|Ireland}} [[2020 